Privacy Policy

Last updated: 2026-01-12

This Privacy Policy explains how this game (“Game”, “we”, “us”) collects and uses information when you play the Game on the Poki platform.

⸻

1. Information We Collect

We do not ask players to provide direct personal identifiers such as name, email address, phone number, or account credentials.

When you play the Game, we may collect technical and gameplay-related data, including:
	•	Gameplay analytics (e.g. session start and end, level progress, retries, in-game actions)
	•	Technical information (e.g. browser type, device type, operating system, language, approximate country or region)
	•	Online identifiers used for analytics and configuration purposes (such as anonymous device or browser identifiers)

This data is collected in an aggregated and non-personal form and is used solely for game improvement.

⸻

2. Purpose of Data Collection

The collected data is used to:
	•	analyze gameplay behavior and game performance
	•	improve game balance, usability, and stability
	•	identify bugs and technical issues
	•	test and evaluate gameplay changes

⸻

3. A/B Testing and Remote Configuration

The Game may use A/B testing and remote configuration (feature flags) to:
	•	enable or disable certain gameplay features
	•	test different gameplay variations
	•	gradually roll out updates or balance changes

These mechanisms rely on anonymous gameplay and technical data only and do not involve identifying individual players.

⸻

4. Third-Party Services (GameAnalytics)

The Game uses GameAnalytics, a third-party analytics service provided by GameAnalytics ApS, to process gameplay analytics, A/B testing, and remote configuration data.
	•	We act as the data controller for data collected through the Game.
	•	GameAnalytics acts as a data processor / service provider, processing data on our behalf.

Information about GameAnalytics’ data protection and privacy practices can be found here:
https://www.gameanalytics.com/trust/privacy-notice

(This link is provided for transparency regarding the service provider. This Privacy Policy describes how player data is handled in this Game.)

⸻

5. Cookies and Local Storage

The Game and its embedded services may use cookies or browser local storage that are necessary for:
	•	basic game functionality
	•	analytics measurement
	•	configuration and feature delivery

No cookies are used to identify players personally.

⸻

6. GDPR (European Economic Area)

If you are located in the European Economic Area (EEA), the processing of analytics data is based on our legitimate interest in improving and maintaining the Game.

We do not collect direct personal identifiers such as names or email addresses.

⸻

7. Children’s Privacy (COPPA)

The Game does not knowingly collect personal information from children under the age of 13.

We do not request names, email addresses, or other direct identifiers.
Any analytics data collected is limited to gameplay and technical information only.

If you believe that personal data from a child has been collected, please contact us so it can be removed.

⸻

8. Data Retention

Analytics and configuration data is retained only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes described in this Privacy Policy and may thereafter be deleted or aggregated.

⸻

9. Contact

If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, you may contact the developer at:

Email: andrey_melnikov_2002@icloud.com
